.TH "uuid_is_valid" 9 "uuid_is_valid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
uuid_is_valid \- checks if a UUID string is valid
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" uuid_is_valid
.BI "(const char *uuid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "uuid" 12
UUID string to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It checks if the UUID string is following the format:
xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx

where x is a hex digit.
.SH "RETURN"
true if input is valid UUID string.
